</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1460,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1604,1629]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Notes.</emphasis>
The brachypronotal morph of this species was described as 
<taxonomicName box="[955,1110,1605,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceperoi">
<emphasis box="[955,1110,1605,1628]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Tetrix ceperoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forma 
<emphasis box="[1192,1329,1604,1629]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">brachyptera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ingrisch" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Ingrisch, S. (1983) Neue Arten und faunistisch bemerkenswerte Nachweise von Orthopteren auf Sardinien. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen, 32 (3), 88 - 94." type="journal article" year="1983">
Ingrisch, 
<number box="[151,207,1640,1664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
from Sardinia (
<bibRefCitation author="Ingrisch" box="[382,548,1640,1665]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Ingrisch, S. (1983) Neue Arten und faunistisch bemerkenswerte Nachweise von Orthopteren auf Sardinien. Nachrichtenblatt der Bayerischen Entomologen, 32 (3), 88 - 94." type="journal article" year="1983">
Ingrisch, 
<number box="[489,548,1640,1664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1983.0">1983</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but according to Article 
<number box="[840,889,1640,1664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="10.2">10.2</number>
of the Code of Zoological Nomenclature (
<collectionCode box="[1362,1432,1640,1664]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">ICZN</collectionCode>
, 
<number box="[151,208,1676,1700]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1999.0">1999</number>
) it is unavailable name. Actually 
<taxonomicName box="[587,742,1677,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceperoi">
<emphasis box="[587,742,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Tetrix ceperoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is divided into two subspecies. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1336,1436,1676,1701]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Thailand</collectingCountry>
we studied well agree with the brief original description and figures of 
<taxonomicName authority="Liang, 1998" authorityName="Liang" authorityYear="1998" box="[1006,1369,1712,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ceperoi" subSpecies="chinensis">
<emphasis box="[1006,1217,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">Tetrix c. chinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Liang" box="[1229,1369,1712,1737]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Liang, G. Q. &amp; Zheng, Z. M. (1998). Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Vol. 12. Orthoptera Tetrigoidea. Science Press, Beijing, 278 pp. [in Chinese, with English summary]" type="book" year="1998">
Liang, 
<number box="[1313,1369,1712,1736]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Guangdong and Henan provinces of 
<collectingCountry box="[589,656,1748,1773]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zheng" box="[676,940,1748,1773]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Liang, G. Q. &amp; Zheng, Z. M. (1998). Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Vol. 12. Orthoptera Tetrigoidea. Science Press, Beijing, 278 pp. [in Chinese, with English summary]" type="book" year="1998">
Zheng &amp; Liang, 
<number box="[880,940,1748,1772]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However the taxonomic relations of the nominotypical subspecies 
<emphasis box="[446,582,1785,1808]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">
T. c. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar, 1887" authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[499,582,1785,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceperoi">ceperoi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar" box="[597,752,1784,1809]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Bolivar, I. (1887) Essai sur les acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 31, 175 - 313." type="journal article" year="1887">
Bolívar, 
<number box="[695,752,1784,1808]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1887.0">1887</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) (distributed in the Mediterranean region) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Liang, 1998" authorityName="Liang" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tetrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ceperoi" subSpecies="chinensis">
<emphasis box="[1278,1436,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="531">T. c. chinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Liang" box="[151,286,1820,1845]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" refString="Liang, G. Q. &amp; Zheng, Z. M. (1998). Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Vol. 12. Orthoptera Tetrigoidea. Science Press, Beijing, 278 pp. [in Chinese, with English summary]" type="book" year="1998">
Liang, 
<number box="[230,286,1820,1844]" pageId="4" pageNumber="531" value="1998.0">1998</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(East Palaearcric and Oriental regions) are still unresolved.
</paragraph>
